I know - old Mr Murphy the policeman, he came round to our house and - he said - he asked me all sorts of - questions, and I was very frightened. And I - I said I wouldn't know them - 
the man again, I said, I - I don't think I would. Anyway, whatever happened - and was a strange thing out, some people opposite - Mrs Green and her family, I've known them for many years, her daughter - until her other - friends had been to a dance at Mam
mersmith Palais - this is not long ago. And - as - as they - when they were in the train - the two girls got at - two girls got out at Shepherds Bush - five of them went altogethe}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16008431\charrsid5646288 
r, two girls got out at Shepher}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15806095\charrsid5646288 d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16008431\charrsid5646288 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15806095\charrsid5646288 
s Bush. Another two got out at - Latimer Road, and Rosemary was the only one that came to Ladbroke Grove.
