This was about - maybe six years ago. And - as - anyway the - they locked him up, and he was a - a - a drunken Irishman, and he was - lodging in Latimer - Telford Road.
 Well - of course - when - Rosemary got indoors she told what had happened and the policeman there, so they said to her mum and dad, well you'll have to get up out of bed and - 'course it was twelve o'clock at night and you must - have to come up to Harro
w
 Road police station. So - they both went up to the police station. So - they kept this man in - in prison all night - in - in the - police station all night, and then they charged him the next day with assault you see, so he said - that this girl - had -
 
had spoken to him in the train, and she'd asked him to come home with her. And he said he'd - she'd been out with him all night and he'd spent all his money on her. Well she'd been with - all the - of course they got all these other girls and this man - h
e got nine months imprisonment.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392069 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15806095\charrsid5646288 But they never found the bloke who attacked you all those years ago?
