e
s we'd have that on a Saturday. For our tea. But - after we'd had our - had our dinner, but always on a Monday we had cold meat - and pickles, baked potatoes in their jackets and bread pudding, or if we didn't have that we'd have - have apples and custard
 
or something like that, and then when we came home at night there was - in the meat tin, the big square bread pudding, help yourself, cut what you want and eat it. Or else in wintertime always in - the fender there there was a whole loaf cut up and - and 
all - all the dripping and - and that out the meat, there's no - no fat in the meat now, you've got to buy fat to cook it in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392069 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15806095\charrsid5646288 Did she ever bake her own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11557774 SF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15806095\charrsid5646288 Sometimes, but - not very often. She used to make scones. Oh yes, we always - we always
 had - she always used to make scones and - I know she used to make brown scones and put - almond in the top, we used to love that and - of course lye sugar on the top of that. We used to love that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392069 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15806095\charrsid5646288 You say your father often wouldn't be home for his midday meal, he'd be out working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11557774 SF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15806095\charrsid5646288 
He would - he would always take sandwiches and then when he came home he always had a hot meal at night. But that was his last meal, he would never have supper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392069 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15806095\charrsid5646288 You'd have your hot meal in the middle of the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11557774 SF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15806095\charrsid5646288 
We'd have our hot meal in the daytime, and we'd have something hot for our tea in the winter. If it was only - as I say, a bread and butter pudding with heaps of fruit in it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392069 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15806095\charrsid5646288 But you'd have supper, you'd have your Nestles milk when you went to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11557774 SF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15806095\charrsid5646288 Pardon? We always had Nestles milk, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392069 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15806095\charrsid5646288 Would you have anything else at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11557774 SF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15806095\charrsid5646288 A biscuit if we wanted it. Or a scone or - piece of bread and butter or whatever we wanted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392069 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15806095\charrsid5646288 You say every Sunday you'd have bacon and eggs, would you have bacon and eggs during the week at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11557774 SF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15806095\charrsid5646288 No, we used to have - perhaps a boiled egg or a fried egg. Well used to get - twelve eggs for a shilling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392069 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15806095\charrsid5646288 Did you have any livestock or anything like that in the garden?
