If - there used to be a girl lived opposite - next door to us and she was very spoilt, Cissy Stag, well I always had very long hair, and every opportunity she
 got she used to pull it. And - one day I - I'd had a tooth out, a back tooth, and I'd got a swollen face and I'm - I would go to school. And - as I was going up - one of those turnings, she got hold of my hair and she pulled it like that. And I punched h
e
r in the face. I - I swished round like that. And I punched her in the face. Of course, she - ran over to her mother and her mother came up the school. And - the headmistress spoke to me about it, and she said, what happened? So I said - Cissy Stag, I sai
d, she pulled my hair, and I punched her. I said, so my teacher - said - I'd just had this tooth out and I'd had an }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16008431\charrsid5646288 abscess}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15806095\charrsid5646288 
 in my face and she said that - I was working and I was in pain and she said I didn't stay away from school, and she said also that Ci
ssy Stag and dipped the - we had desks then with little inkwells in. Well in front of Cissy Stag sat a little girl, Kathleen Bartlett and she had golden lovely golden hair, she dipped all the ends of that girls hair in the ink well. So the teacher told - 
told Miss Mant. So Miss Mant said - go away, she said, and she said to the mother, don't come here complaining, she said, teach your child how to behave. She said, behave like a child not a cannibal.
