e home - my mother said did we enjoy it and we were having our tea, and - or our supperwhatever it may be, we were all sitting there, and - I - I said I think God's very wicked. Why do you think God's wicked? I said, all those lovely lions and tigers, I s
a
id, they've got miles and miles and miles - where they live, and then I said they're all put in cages, and I - I said it's wicked and God's wicked to let them do it. So my mother told us then, she said, it's not God. It's - it's the man that does this. So
