second hand bicycle, and we were only allowed to ride it on the sideway, of course there wasn't the traffic there is now. And then - when I was thirteen - I had a - chance - choice to have a - a new bicycle or a watch. And - I said, well as I'm going down
 
to - stay with auntie - I'll - I want a watch and I had - a - lovely watch and a strap. But I can never wear a watch, it stops immediately. And - I used to have it on a little fob in my - in my pocket. I - I made it out of a bit of wash leather, I tucked 
-
 tucked inside like that, and I cut a hole in, and I used to have it in that pocket on a little fob, on a little - piece of black satin. But - I didn't want - I didn't want the bicycle, we - used to have such fights over it. I don't know what became of th
at, I - I think we had punctures galore with that. We had to mend them ourselves.
