an go out to play. But she said, the - Albert was the - was his brother, he - he shelled the peas quickly, so his mother told him he could go out to play. They were allowed to run in the streets. And - my husband had to take a dress home - only up - somew
here up the road there, well - that boy went up - out to play with this boy Johnson, and they got on the riverbank - on the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2359735\charrsid5646288 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
