said - I wonder where he's gone. So my mother said, well he - he must be a naughty boy, he's run away somewhere. So - anyway she said - come along, she said, you mustn't think anymore about it. Well the next morning going to school - I went round to Mrs F
r
eeman's. And of course the - we heard then that - his dad had come home from work, and he wasn't home and he went to the police - and they - found the boys had suffocated in this mud. He said you couldn't recognise his face and - that - how they knew it w
as his - boy, his face was all cut to piece, how they knew it was his boy they recognised him because their mother used to make all their trousers and - and - coats you know until }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2359735\charrsid5646288 
