ries and all sorts of things, and on the counter there used to be a big glass box, and inside that was lumps of jelly with coconut in, and sometimes - I must shut that a minute - sometimes he'd - can't bear that round my waist - sometimes he'd say, old Mr
 
Bryant, you keep an eye on the shop, my luv, perhaps he'd go out to the toilet, he didn't tell me where he went, and I'd stand there behind that counter and - I used to think, oh I'm so clever. And then when he come back I used to get - five or six of the
s
e - lumps of jelly with coconut in. Well when the shop was sold old Mr Bryant died - we moved across the road into Telford Road, and we had the top half of the house there and old Mr Rogers - he used to sit in the - in the shop mending shoes. And - we - '
