\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392069 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15806095\charrsid5646288 What did she think of your husband?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11557774 SF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15806095\charrsid5646288 She never liked him. Oh she - she didn't d
islike him but she disliked their ways of living. 'Cos the father was always drunk. And the mother, she used to go - she used to go with Mrs O'Shaunessy that lived in - in the - opposite road there, they used to go to church - church - and - that was a bo
y
s college then, St Charles College - and the corner up there where - the last - house here before you get to the Eagle public house, that was a bakers and we used to come out and see the boys - coming in there and helping themselves to cakes out the windo
w
, eat them you know. Sometimes we'd get one, sometimes we wouldn't, but - those were the sort of things that we were amused at but - we were never allowed - allowed out at night. Not - go home from school and - you didn't go out unless you came to evening
 - you know, to church - to the mission, or to go to the Guild, but other than that -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392069 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15806095\charrsid5646288 Did your father ever take an active interest in politics do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11557774 SF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15806095\charrsid5646288 Pardon? No. He was a Liberal. I always remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392069 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15806095\charrsid5646288 Did he ever talk about why he was a liberal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11557774 SF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15806095\charrsid5646288 We never knew anything about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392069 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15806095\charrsid5646288 Did he vote in any elections before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11557774 SF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15806095\charrsid5646288 
I can remember - I can't remember but I can never remember my father on any occasion - ever going out in the evening when he came home from work, un
less he went out with - with my mother, but where they went I don't know. That's when old Cheetham - Mr Cheetham used to tell us all about - the boats and - how they used to get people on the boats and take all their money and then the boat would go down 
i
n the ocean. Oh and our used to nearly pop out and then the pilots got on the boats, oh - we knew it all then. But - that's all we ever knew, but - I can tell you one thing, myself and my two sisters - we - we were - better educated than some of the kids 
o
f today, because - some - some of them can't spell, and - they can't even speak plainly and they can't write a letter, but of course you can only blame that onto the television, there's no conversation, and the typewriter, there's no - handwritten letters
, only the signature.
