n that class, she'd got a beautiful - lovely brown dog, Rover, and - as I walked into that - into the hall, I said goodbye to my mum, and I said come and see me playtime won't you, look through the railings, so she said, yes, I'll come and see you playtim
e
, look through the railing, 'course the gates were shut. So - 'course I - I was the only one that went to school you see, my sisters were - not old enough. Oh dear, mum used to come - and have a look at me through the railings for a little while. And - I 
took to that Mrs Wilson - the first time I ever - ever saw her. And right up until I was married - and I met her - on - Ladbroke Grove Station, she used to live at Hammersmith, and I met her on }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
