pstairs one was the worst. She had short hair, grey - oh - she was a crab. Had to stand in the hall always for - assembly. And do you know - long after I was married my name was up on the board there - where - the scholarship, different ages, and - yes, a
n
d - Mrs Frazer, Scotch, she always used to wear a collar and tie, short hair, and a long skirt and always flat heeled shoes. Well one look from her my dear you'd perish. And Mrs Reid - Miss Reid was my teacher in the - in the sixth - class, there was - cl
ass one, two, three, four, five, sixth, seventh and ex-seventh. Well - all the scholarship girls was in the ex-seventh you see - we passed before we got to the ex-seventh. And - I know - Miss Reid was}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
