to sit for an exam and - I - I can't remember now what I had to do I - I had to sit - sit for this exam and - I passed, the same as I did - up at the - Associated Cinemas, about twelve of us interviewed, I was fifty - and - he said, we'll let you know - }
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid281643\charrsid5646288 we'll let you know withi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15806095\charrsid5646288 
n - two or three days, he said, I've got a few more people to see. So he said, how long were you at the hospital? I said, twenty years. And - he said - why did you leave? Well I said, I - they offered me another job when they took me 
out of the laboratory I said, and - I wouldn't take it, I said, I didn't actually refuse, but I said I said that I would be examined - up at the - Westminster, I said - I'll - I - got an appointment up there with this Doctor Davis, so he said, the only wo
r
k that you can do Mrs Freeman, he said, will be - clerical work, because, he said you mustn't go in that laboratory again. There's something you're allergic to, 'cos I woke up in the morning and from there to there my arms were that colour. And it was all
 
swollen and I never knew what it was, I got some germ in me. Well he said, you could - go back in the sewing room. Well, I said, I can't go back in the sewing room, I said, because that comes under a Board of Trade. Well - between the times - the laundry 
w
as closed there, it was bombed. So - for about a fortnight or three weeks - I did all the book keeping for all the nurses laundry. Had to check it all in and check it all out. Well that was about three weeks I did that, and then I - was called up to Count
y
 Hall. I went and saw this Doctor Davis at County Hall and he said the only thing is, he said, will be - that - you'll have to go on the - clerical work. He said, you're a very good writer, he said, and you - you've done lots of work in there, I said, yes
,
 well - considering I kept all the records I said, we only had one technician then, they've got about twenty now, so - he said, what did you do there? I said, I - I said, I did centrafusion and - made capillary for pets and I said I did - all the book - a
ll the - book keeping, the results of post morte}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid281643\charrsid5646288 m}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15806095\charrsid5646288 
 tests and - all in the register. I said, I loved the work very much. But I said of course if I'm not allowed to go in there and touch the specimens and some of 'em are pretty rotten I can tell you - I couldn't do it now.
\par 
